You are in the Northern Woods.

You can see a Twisted Oak, a leaf litter and Your Dog.

You can go north or south.

You are on a path in the woods that runs North to South, the trees are densely packed, shards of sunlight stab through the small gaps in the canopy, it is humid in here. The floor of the forest is thick with leaf litter from countless autumns.

> x oak

> x oak

An enormous oak tree lies to the side of the path. Its trunk and branches are twisted into contorted and tortured shapes like writhing serpents.

Nestled into the base of the tree is a small blue door.
> x door

> x door

A small arched shaped door around 2 foot high and painted a pale pastel blue colour. There is a handwritten sign next to it.
> x sign

> x sign

In perfect copperplate the sign reads,

 'Residence of Gnome Chompsky, Master Weaver and Tailor, No Free Papers, Thank You'
> x litter

> x litter

The floor of the woods is carpeted in a deep layer of dead leaves, ranging in colour from a deep copper to pale yellow
