You can go north or south.

You are on a path in the woods that runs North to South, the trees are densely packed, shards of sunlight stab through the small gaps in the canopy, it is humid in here. The floor of the forest is thick with leaf litter from countless autumns.

> knock on door

> knock on door

You knock politely on the door, you can hear the sound of someone running downstairs, the door is yanked open, and standing in the door is a Gnome, behind him you can see stairs leading up into the heart of the tree.

"Hello traveller!", says the Gnome, "What can I do for you?"

Dylan wanders over and sniffs curiously at the Gnome, the Gnome chuckles and pats him on the nose.

"I'd invite you in, but you're just too big!" says the Gnome
> give reeds to gnome

> give reeds to gnome

"Ah river reeds, perfect for rope making, let me sort that out for you". With his quick and nimble fingers the Gnome weaves the reeds together with astonishing speed. He hands you a long coil of strong rope.
> x rope

> x rope

A strong coil of rope weaved from reeds
> ask gnome about bridge

> ask gnome about bridge

"Yes I've seen it, must have been some heavy rainfall in the hills. Don't try swimming across, the current is far too strong and the water is deathly cold. Don't hold your breath for the council to fix the bridge anytime soon, all the infrastructure taxes get spent in Lost."
