A bamboo fishing rod, with a cork handle. It has a line and hook, and a now fully functional reel.
> give apple to horse

> give apple to horse

You place the apple in the flat palm of your hand and offer it up to the horse. Its lips tickle your hand as it picks it up, it munches it noisily. You smell the tart tang of the apple as it's masticated.

The horse eyes you and gently snorts. You've made a friend.
