> x mouse

> x mouse

It's Gerald the Mouse, he's wearing a smart grey suit and half-moon spectacles, and he's carrying a small metal lever.
> give cheese to mouse

> give cheese to mouse

You break a small piece off the lump of cheese and give it to the mouse. The mouse reaches up with it's little front paws, grabs the cheese, gobbles it down, then gives a tiny squeak of appreciation.

Gerald opens the lid of the piano and jumps inside, there a commotion of plinking, plonking and squeaking. Then Gerald reappears, jumps on to the keyboard and plays a sweet rendition of "Old Amsterdam" by running around and stamping on the keys with his feet.

The Landlord gives a small slow sarcastic round of applause. The Mouse takes a bow, gives the Landlord the finger and dashes off.
> play piano

> play piano

You sit down at the piano, and remembering the message in the bottle you pull out the scroll and begin to play the score, "Adagio in G minor by Albinoni".

Your sight-reading skills are rusty but your fingers somehow remember the tune, the haunting melody fills the pub. Looking over to the bar you can see the Landlord's astonished face.

When you've finished the piece the Landlord walks over, inspects the script and says, "Well, well, well, I should have recognised you, but its been a long time. Listen the armed forces still loyal to the King are camped to the far south on the border with Somewhere, we need to get a message to them to attack tomorrow at dawn"

"You've done well getting here to far, take this note and get it to the Loyalist as fast as possible", "I'm off to organise the resistance forces still hiding out in the city"
> x message

> x message

A tiny scroll of paper, in minute writing it reads:

 "Attack at dawn, resistance ready, J.J"
> x coins

> x coins

Three silver 1 zilch coins, the currency of Nowhere. They have a portrait of the skeletal 'Bony' King on the obverse and an Axe on the other side. Inscribed around the edge it reads, "Quidquid latinae dictum set, altrum sonar "
> give hair to gnome

> give hair to gnome

"Well, well, well, what do we have here! Giant's hair, rare stuff this, makes the best rope known to man, let's see what we can do"

With astonishing speed and dexterity the Gnome twists and plaits and weaves the strands of hair together into a long, thin, but incredibly strong rope, he hands it to you.

> w

> w

You are in a City Plaza.

You can see a Fountain and Your Dog.

You can go north, east or west.

Large open public space, and the heart of the city. Doesn't seem to be many people around though, perhaps they are hiding from the army.

On the south side of the square there is a row of soldiers on horseback, blocking the path to the castle drawbridge.

In the centre of the square there is a fountain, underneath which you can see an emaciated pigeon pecking at a few biscuit crumbs.

> w

> w

You are in a Beppe's Pizzaria.

You can see Beppe, a Counter and Your Dog.

You can go east.

There is a heavenly smell of dough, cheese and woodsmoke in here. Behind the counter you can see the owner Beppe removing pizzas from the oven with a long peal.

> x Beppe

> x Beppe

A dark and swarthy type with a roman nose and a friendly grin. He's wearing chef whites and a white cap.
> x counter

> x counter

A wooden counter with a hammered zinc top, there is a sign reading,

'Beppe's stupendo pizza

Piccolo - 1 Zilch

Medio - 2 Zilch

Gigantesco! - 3 Zilch'

> give coins to Beppe

> give coins to Beppe

"Grazie mille!" says Beppe,

He scoops a huge pizza out of the oven with his peal, places it in a cardboard tray, closes the lid and hands it to you.
> x pizza

> x pizza

A huge cardboard pizza box with a picture of Venice on the front, steam is escaping from the lovely pizza inside, it smells heavenly.
> e

> e

You are in a City Plaza.

You can see a Fountain and Your Dog.

You can go north, east or west.

Large open public space, and the heart of the city. Doesn't seem to be many people around though, perhaps they are hiding from the army.

On the south side of the square there is a row of soldiers on horseback, blocking the path to the castle drawbridge.

In the centre of the square there is a fountain, underneath which you can see an emaciated pigeon pecking at a few biscuit crumbs.

> give pizza to Jon

> give pizza to Jon

"Fuck me, now you're talking" says the pigeon...*hack* *splutter*, "I haven't eaten properly in weeks"

The pigeon dives into the pizza, there is a blur of wings, feathers, feet and beak, small pieces of cheese and dough fly into the air. After a few minutes the pizza is gone and a fatter looking pigeon is now standing there.
> give horehound to Jon

> give horehound to Jon

"What this herbal shite when it's at home?" Says Jon, "Only joking, horehound weed aint' it. The Pigeon pecks a small corner of leaf,  "well it tastes like crap but I'll try anything to shift this damn cough"

The pigeon pecks and chews at the leaves for a few minutes, and his breathing seems to ease, "Thanks" he says, "Don't take my swearing personally, you're a decent fucker"
> give message to Jon

> give message to Jon

You place the message in a small leather tube on the pigeon's leg

"Fuck's sake" says the Pigeon. "Another message to deliver, well if it means the city gets back to normal and the litter returns I guess I'm game".

The pigeon takes a long run up, beats its wings furiously and manages to get it's pizza laden body airborne, as it disappears South you can hear its faint voice on the wind, "Fuuuuck Yooouu!"

Just at that moment General D'sarray enters the City Plaza.

You hear a small clanking noise and looking down you see that Gerald the Mouse has appeared by your side
> x General

> x General

An ugly bloated porcine looking army general. His drab olive uniform is festooned with medals and gold braiding, he has a swagger stick under one arm and is wearing black jackboots, and a black hat with a red front and more gold braiding.
> x mouse

> x mouse

It's Gerald the Mouse, this time he is wearing a full suit of armour, including helmet with the visor down. He is holding a lance in one hand and a shield in the other.
> give cheese to mouse

> give cheese to mouse

You break a small piece off the lump of cheese and give it to the mouse. The mouse reaches up with it's little front paws which are wearing adorable tiny gauntlets, takes the cheese, raises his visor and gobbles it down, and then gives a tiny squeak of appreciation, and with a salute closes his visor.

Aiming his lance at the General on the other side of the square, Gerald runs at full charge.

Just as Gerald reaches the General he is spotted, the General takes a swing with his foot and with sickening force kicks Gerald so hard that he goes flying into the air and over the castle walls.

Dylan wimpers, tears well in your eyes and a violent rage burns in your heart.

"rodent scum" grunts the General.

> attack general

> attack general

In your grief and anger you grab hold of your axe and charge recklessly at the General with a furious Dylan by your side, yelling "Kiss my shiny metal axe you bastard!" but you are quickly overpowered by the guards and knocked unconscious.
