> x king

> x king

The 'bony' king of Nowhere, stick thin, (you'd find more meat on a butchers pencil), his emaciated face is even more drawn than the last time you saw him. His regal red robes hang off him, he's sat uncomfortably on the straw.
> x straw

> x straw

Blackened filthy straw, it stinks and is sticky to the touch
> x bars

> x bars

Thick iron bars, it would take a month of Sundays to file your way though one of them, even if you had the tools
> i

> i

You are not carrying anything.
> speak to king

> speak to king

"Hello my child, its a joy to see you, even under such grim circumstances"
> ask king about general

> ask king about general

"He's always been a hawk for conflict, but never thought he'd betray me, barks all the time, but he finally bit." "His men only fear and don't love him though, his power base is weak."
> move straw

> move straw

Moving aside the filthy straw reveals the stoney floor, but wait one of the stones is loose!
> move stone

> move stone

You grab hold of the loose stone, with a great deal of wiggling you manage to remove it, after a lot of hard work you manage to remove a few more, until there is a hole barely big enough to fit through
> d

> d

With a great deal of struggling, writhing and wriggling you manage to squeeze through the hole, your Father and Dylan have far less trouble and follow behind you.

You land on some filthy straw
You are in a Prison Cell 37927b.

You can see a pile of stones and Your Dog.

A dark and dank prison cell, with filthy straw on the hard stone floor, the walls of the cell is in the form of an iron cage.

> x stones

> x stones

The stones you removed to make the hole, what a waste of time that was.
> z

> z

Time passes.
> z

> z

Time passes.
> z

> z

Time passes.
You hear a rattle of keys and a guard appears at the door to the cell, behind him you can see two armed soldiers "Time to meet your maker, traitor scum"

You are lead out of the cell to the castle courtyard. Dylan brushes against your leg for reassurance as you walk.
You are in a Courtyard.

You can see Your Dog.

You are lead into the Castle courtyard, the pale blue light in the East heralds that the arrival of dawn is nigh. You, the King and Dylan are led to platform and each tied to stake. You can't believe they are going to kill Dylan as well.

"I'm so sorry" says the King, "I know you never wanted any part in the politics of the Kingdom, I'm sorry I brought you back here, I didn't know who else to send the letter to"

"That's OK Dad", you reply.

The first rays of dawn hit the courtyard and make you blink in the light.

Facing you is a firing squad and General D'sarray, "Silence traitors!" barks the General.

"Men on my mark take aim!", "Aim", the squad raise their guns, "Ready", you brace yourself, at that moment the sky darkens, confused the General looks up, and is hit smack in the temple by what looks like a metal boomerang, he collapses to the floor like a sack of spuds. More boomerangs rain down on the firing squad.

Looking up you see it's Batbat! and who's is that riding on his back but Gerald! He's wearing some weird rubber suit with a red letter R on the front.

There is a thundering of hooves and the Loyal forces storm into the courtyard, rounding up the remaining soldiers.

"You saved the Kingdom my child!" says the King, "You're welcome to it" you reply, "I'm off home to the North", "Come on Dylan, let's go!", "Thank fuck for that" replies Dylan.

**************************************************************************
Congratulations, you have completed The Bony King of Nowhere, thanks for playing!

The END

